{# Shared base for Alpha-HRP LLM summary prompts (US + India).

The math-aware sections -- Stage 1 alpha rank table, sticky outcome
(K_in / K_hold semantics, kept/fillers/evicted), and Stage 2 final
allocation -- live here so US and India cannot disagree on what the
numbers mean. Market-specific narrative (sector hints, trading account
context, JSON paragraph schema) lives in child templates via the
{% block analyst_intro %}, {% block strategy_overview %}, and
{% block instructions %} overrides.

Children only need to override:

* analyst_intro -- one line of "You are a financial analyst specializing
  in <market>" framing.
* strategy_overview_extras -- optional bullets that close the strategy
  overview with market context (e.g. "Trading account: Alpaca paper").
* instructions -- the full JSON schema block (4 paragraphs) so each
  market can name its sectors, currency, etc.

Everything else (rank tables, sticky stats, HRP weights) is one
implementation. #}
{% block analyst_intro %}You are a financial analyst specializing in equity markets and quantitative portfolio construction.{% endblock %}
Analyze a two-stage "Alpha-HRP" portfolio allocation for the {{ universe }} universe.

## Strategy Overview
- **Stage 1 (Alpha screen)**: PatchTST (OHLCV transformer) was run on the full {{ universe }} universe ({{ predicted_count }}/{{ requested_count }} stocks produced valid weekly-return forecasts) using model version `{{ model_version }}`. Symbols are then ranked by predicted_weekly_return_pct descending.
- **Rank-band sticky selection**: From those ranks, an asymmetric rank-band picks the final {{ top_n }} stocks. Entry threshold is rank <= {{ top_n }} (K_in); a previously-held stock is **retained** as long as its current rank is <= {{ hold_threshold }} (K_hold), even if it slipped out of the entry zone. Goal: capture alpha without churning friction every time mid-rank names reshuffle.
- **Stage 2 (Risk-parity sizing)**: HRP was run on the {{ top_n }} chosen stocks using a {{ stage2.lookback_days }}-day lookback (~{{ (stage2.lookback_days / 252) | round(1) }} year). After HRP's covariance/data-alignment step, {{ stage2.symbols_used }} stocks ended up with a non-zero weight; any names dropped by HRP are listed in `symbols_excluded`.
- As-of Date: {{ stage2.as_of_date }}
{% block strategy_overview_extras %}{% endblock %}

